My name is Alana, and I am a passionate, equity-minded, communication studies professor. I have dedicated my career to exploring the intersections of communication, power, and social justice.

As a professor, I am committed to creating an inclusive and equitable classroom environment where all students feel seen, heard, and valued. I believe that effective communication is essential for creating positive social change, and I work tirelessly to empower students with the tools and knowledge they need to become effective communicators and advocates for equity.

name: Christine Widden
about:
I'm a graduate student majoring in Computer Science at Cal Poly in San Luis Obispo! 

I've had a passion for programming ever since I played around with MIT's Scratch in middle school. Every project is a puzzle!

I'm equipped with endless hours of experience in a variety of programming languages from C to Javascript, as well as a deeper understanding of what makes the code we write actually work, from the processor through the Operating System all the way up to the building blocks of the programming languages themselves.

In my free time I like to play video games, watch other people play videogames (speedruns especially!) and go on Tabletop RPG adventures with my friends.
